MESSAGE.value: Refactored the initial commit to the java source directory. Was placed in test directory by accident.
refactored console out of method names.
Agent interface created with some basic methods.
swapped out unrequired Double format for int before it gets out of hand. Doubles are not required and int's can be presented as decimal to a user. Int have fewer rounding errors.
added a the launcher and started creating a text adventure style system to run the game.
removed setView method within consoles as each console will have a dedicated view specific for the console.

shifted the classes around so that the data persistence and view for each type of game are together within a single module. Enabling interfaces to be extracted and new versions of the system to be created.
Renamed some classes and created an interface to make a clear distinction between what a programmer needs to implement to create a BossFight system.
created a temporary enum class as an experiment.
Reset enum changes, initial factory creation and the things Joe refactored and ruined using a class name 'A' for about five seconds.
using the interface of BossFightView instead of the TextAdventureView to assign a field
created a factory for making an agent.
refactored some names. Currently an agent isn't created with any stats. A Rulebook must be injected into the factory and the factory used.
rulebook now injected into an agent factory.
created some lovely methods within agent regarding being attacked, and dying.
